      <bioghist id="aspace_c3d84356b8dbaf6d5be23ceb69245bea">
         <head>JULES SUPERVIELLE (1884-1960)</head>
         <p>Jules Supervielle, a poet, dramatist, and short-story writer of Basque descent, was born in Montevideo, Uruguay. He died in Paris in 1960.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ce44b6f5210d2997ef7c87f876d49a35">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This finding aid encompasses accessions of single manuscripts and small groups of manuscripts and other papers, by or pertaining to Jules Supervielle, acquired by the library from a variety of sources. Materials incorporated into the collection prior to August 1999 have been organized into two series. <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref12">Series I, Writings</ref>, contains drafts of various plays and poems, and a printed version of <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Débarcadères</part>
            </title>, which has been annotated by Supervielle. <ref actuate="onrequest" show="replace" target="ref34">Series II, Letters</ref>, contains letters from Supervielle to Isabelle Clarke and Elie Richard, as well as drafts of letters to Felisberto Hernández and an unidentified correspondent.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
